      "content": "While a living wage sounds ideal, the data shows it is often a losing battle for small rural businesses because the cost increase is rarely offset by a proportional rise in local spending power. In many cases, forcing these businesses to raise prices or cut staff ultimately hurts the very community you want to support by reducing the number of available jobs and driving up the cost of living for everyone. The only scenario where it might work is if the local government simultaneously provides massive subsidies or tax breaks to offset the financial strain, which is a complex political solution rather than a simple policy fix.",
